  <div class="" style="background-color: #f1e8df; color: #6667AB; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: .2rem; text-align: center; display: flex; justify-content: center;">
    
    <br>
    
    ACCESSIBILITY
    
    <br>
    <br>
    
    It is widely believed that disability is either
    <br>
    the result of a rare inherited trait or being careless.
    <br>
    Yet, the truth is disability is an unpredictable fate that can happen to anyone.
    
    <br>
    <br>
    
    Rarely do the abled think of the disabled. Why should we
    <br>
    when the disabled account for a very small percentage of the population?
    
    <br>
    <br>
    
    Building an inclusive world in which the disabled
    <br>
    have equal accessibility to physical and digital spaces
    <br>
    means that we can all thrive together
    <br>
    regardless of what is to come for each of us.
    
    <br>
    <br>
    
  </div>
  
  &nbsp;
